text:
Aroma: very small;
Appearance: nice bottle with porcelain cap. Copper coloured. quickly fanishing creamy head;
Flavor: malt, some bitter,some sour;
Palate: light body, soft carbonation, waterly finish;
Overall: nice Altbeer but less than Uerige or Schlüssel;
Bought at Trinkgut (Kleve, Germany)
